==Mandarín==

===Etymology===
Mandarín "天命" (''Pīnyīn:'' [[Tiānmìng]]) ~ ''(literally)'' '''[[Mandate of Heaven]]'''

===Proper Noun===
{{Wikipedia}}
#The doctrine of political [[legitimisation]] used by the kings of the [[Shang]] dynasty and by the Emperors of China. It asserts that Heaven would bless the reign of a just ruler, but would withdraw such a mandate if that ruler were to become an unjust one. Compare the [[Divine Right of Kings]].
#The first era name of the [[Qing]] Empire.

